Task: deloying an application on NGINX in AWS EC2 Ubuntu

1. update repositories
apt-get update

2. install nginx
apt-get install nginx

3. install and enable Firewall
apt-get install ufw
ufw app list
ufw allow "Nginx HTTP"

4. check nginx status
systemctl status nginx

5. check the welcome page 
(localhost)
or 
(127.0.0.1)
or
(instance public IP)

6 change to welcome page
cd /var/www/html

7. change to another name
mv index.nginx-debian.html <anyname>

8. clone index.html and index.php from github repo
git clone <repo name>

9. copy index.* files to directory /var/www/html

10. if needed create new file:
vim index.html
esc
:wg!

11. restart nginx
systemctl restart nginx

12. reaload web browser page
________________________________________
# Activity logs of nginx
# access logs
tail /var/log/nginx/access.log

# error logs
tail /var/log/nginx/error.lg 
